教師授課計劃表(學生課表查詢部份)

東吳大學教師授課計劃表
檔案產生時間：2016/2/26 下午 01:57:57本表如有異動，於4小時內自動更新



一、課程基本資料 Course Information


科目名稱 Course Title：(中文)亞太區域發展城中全英語
		(英文)REGION DEVELOPMENT IN ASIA PACIFIC
開課學期 Semester：104學年度第1學期開課班級 Class：國際學術


授課教師 Instructor：李元和 LEEYUAN-HO
		


科目代碼 Course Code：BNA05001
單全學期 Semester/Year：單
分組組別 Section：城中全英語


人數限制 Class Size：55
必選修別 Required/Elective：選
學分數 Credit(s)：2


星期節次 Day/Session：  二56　
前次異動時間 Time Last Edited：104年09月15日09時05分



二、指定教科書及參考資料 Textbooks and Reference(請修課同學遵守智慧財產權，不得非法影印)


●指定教科書 Required Texts
		●參考書資料暨網路資源 Reference Books and Online Resources1. APEC journals2. The Asia Foundation 3. Asia-Pacific Review4. Asia-Pacific Forum 5. Asia-Pacific Economic Literature6. ADB working papers7. APO Annual Report, Asian Productivity Organization8. Asian Survey 9. Bloomberg Businessweek10. The Economist


三、教學目標 Objectives


一、	讓同學能瞭解亞太地區在國際經貿環境所處的地位及其所扮演的角色。二、	讓同學能瞭解亞太地區各國之經貿現況。三、	讓同學能瞭解亞太地區內部產業間的互補和競爭狀況。四、	讓同學能瞭解提升亞太地區產業發展之優勢及其限制之因素。五、	讓同學能瞭解在經濟全球化的趨勢下，亞太各國產業政策之因應。1. Let the students understand the position of the Asia-Pacific region in international trade environment and its role played.2. Let the students understand the trade status of countries in the Asia Pacific region.3. Let the students understand the situation of complementarity and competition of the industry within the Asia-Pacific region.4. Let the students understand the advantages of upgrading industrial development and its limits in the Asia-Pacific region.5. Let the students understand the industrial policy of the Asia-Pacific countries in response to the trend of economic globalization. 


 


四、課程內容 Course Description


●整體敘述 Overall Description本課程將從亞太地區各國之人文、地理環境、氣候、文化及產業加以介紹，並強調區域內各國經貿制度及產業政策之發展，從而瞭解各國產業之優劣勢及亞太內部產業之競爭與互補，此外，也將探討在經濟全球化的趨勢下亞太各國在制度和政策上之調整和因應之道。This course will introduce to cover humanities, geographic environment, climate, culture, and industry and also emphasize on the economic/trade system and industrial developing policies inside the Asia Pacific region. Based on these, we can understand the advantage and disadvantage of the industry in each Asia Pacific country as well as the competition and complementarity intra-industry in Asia Pacific region. In addition, the course will explore the way of the adjustment and deal with the systems and policies in Asia Pacific countries under the trend of economic globalization.

